title: Ground News - Abu Dhabi's non-oil economy grew by 7.7% in the third quarter
text:
Summary by elfagr.org The real non-oil GDP of the Emirate of Abu Dhabi grew 7.7% in the third quarter, compared to the levels of the same period in 2022. According to data released on Friday, December 29th, real non-oil GDP grew by 8.6% during the first 9 months of 2023. Despite market fluctuations Share menu More
